{
  "stem": "19895.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was something tremendous in my younger years as a boy to, to be on a train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I enjoyed every bit of the trip.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in the town of [NON-ENGLISH] where my vacation took place, I have fond memories of having a wonderful time and meeting some relatives of my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My grandmother's brother, Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Beno Friedmann, was an elderly man, a retired physician, who-- briefly mentioning, it was an interesting story.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because he returned to Hungary after having some many, many years of practicing as a physician in the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he was a very kind man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I remember that second uncle, my grandmother's brother, very well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And his wife, who was a teacher-- and at age six or even sooner, age five, I think I was in that town on summer vacation-- she is the one who taught me how to read Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I read Hebrew probably, in the beginning of my learning years of, of, of reading, probably just as good or better than I learned how to read Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because she was a Hebrew teacher.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she was the one who taught me to read Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When I got to school, the elementary school in Hungary was a public school which I attended.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And religious education for Jewish boys was separate from the rest of the class.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because in that class of some 20-some people, we had only three of us or four of us who were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we had once a week a separate religious hour, which was sponsored by the Jewish community of the city.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it came very well that I was ahead of everybody.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because when everybody had great struggling learning to read Hebrew, which was part of the education, I already was able to read.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
